    "assumptions": [
      "Canonical reporting metric is equal-weight by vignette after equal-weight pooling across runs within each vignette; extra trials within a vignette must not increase its weight.",
      "Domains currently have equal vignette counts, so equal-domain and global equal-vignette summaries are equivalent for the target reports.",
      "The methodology change should standardize existing model-reporting surfaces, not redesign unrelated analytics surfaces."
    ],
    "summary": "Requirements are stable. This feature standardizes model-reporting win rates on the equal-vignette methodology: average runs equally within each vignette, then average vignettes equally. Because domains have equal vignette counts, the cross-domain summaries should align once count-based recomputation is removed.",
